-- U.S. Stocks Rise as Boehner Talks With Obama Were ’Constructive’
-- B y   M i c h a e l   P .   R e g a n
-- 2012-11-16T16:54:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-16/u-s-stocks-rise-as-boehner-talks-with-obama-were-constructive-.html
U.S. stocks rose, erasing earlier
losses, as House Speaker  John Boehner  said he had
“constructive” talks with President Barack Obama about he
budget and would accept government revenue increases coupled
with spending cuts.  The Standard & Poor’s 500 Index added 0.3 percent at
1,356.73 at 11:53 a.m. in New York after earlier sliding as much
as 0.7 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
